                            <comment id="15721991" author="anoop.hbase" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2016 11:12:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When we created MBB, we intentionally avoided many checks to save those costs..  Now as per the new usage ways, if they are needed, we can add.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15722000" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2016 11:16:08 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now as per the new usage ways, if they are needed, we can add.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ya it is needed now. &lt;br/&gt;
In rpcServer we have now&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    ByteBuffer[] bufsFromPool = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (bbs.size() &amp;gt; 0) {
      bufsFromPool = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ByteBuffer[bbs.size()];
      bbs.toArray(bufsFromPool);
    }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (remain &amp;gt; 0) {
      bbs.add(ByteBuffer.allocate(remain));
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now this remain could be anything. So it is better we make MBB more robust.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15722001" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2016 11:16:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BTW is the patch fine with you - &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=anoopsamjohn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;anoopsamjohn&quot;&gt;Anoop Sam John&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15722063" author="anoop.hbase" created="Mon, 5 Dec 2016 11:51:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So u r saying abt the MBB create and usage in the write path now..  So this means we flow expect MBB to have an int but those many bytes not there!.  This can happen if the incoming req bytes were some how truncated..   But then we have check much before these processing..  We have 1st 4 bytes of req as the total req bytes length.  We make MBB as per this length and then read into it.  If we are not able to get those many bytes, we will throw exception there itself..   So I would say chance of this issue coming in write path also very less.. or not possible..&lt;br/&gt;
For completion of the API as such I am ok to add the check..  As said , many checks possible in MBB, we avoided..   So this way it would be possible to see many gaps.. Am not sure whether to add checks all those places..  Am ok to add this check.  Not a costly thing at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
